SIMPLE: harrier
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harrier
<hw>Har"ri*er</hw> <pr>(-⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Hare</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a
small breed of hounds, used for hunting hares.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>harier</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harrier</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Harrier
<hw>Har"ri*er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Harry</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who harries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of several species of hawks
or buzzards of the genus <gen>Circus</gen> which fly low and
<xex>harry</xex> small animals or birds, -- as the European marsh
harrier (<spn>Circus aeruginosus</spn>), and the hen harrier
(<spn>Circus cyaneus</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Harrier hawk</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>one of
several species of American hawks of the genus
<gen>Micrastur</gen>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harrisia</ent>⟦br⟧
